Head.
Antenna with 53 segments; middle antennomere s 3.0 × longer than wide (6:2); third antennomeres 1.1 × fourth (9:8); preapical antennomere 1.25 × apical antennomere (5:4); maxillary palp 1.5 × as long as height of head (43:29); width of face 0.9 × length of face and clypeus combined (15:16) (
Fig. 25
); malar space 1.25 × as long as mandible basal width (5:4); mandible basal width 0.5 × as long as hypoclypeal depression (4:8); malar suture present (
Fig. 25
); distance between tentorial pits 4.0 × distance between pits and eyes (8:2); in dorsal view, height of eye 5.0 × as long as temple (15:3); in lateral view, width of eye 4.0 × as long as temple (14:3.5) (
Fig. 26
); ocelli rather large, POL:OD:OOL=2:4:3; distance between front and hind ocelli 0.7 × as long as OOL (2:3) (
Fig. 24
). Face rugose; frons flat, with transverse striae near antennal sockets; vertex with fine transverse striae; temple coriaceous.

Metasoma.
First tergite 1.1 × as long as apical width (34:30) (
Fig. 28
); median length of second tergite 1.9 × than third (29:15); ovipositor sheath 0.85 × as long as hind basitarsus (23:27) and 0.13 × fore wing. First metasomal tergite with complete median carina, longitudinally striate (
Fig. 28
); second tergite with median carina in 0.8 basal tergite, striate as first tergite; third-fourth tergites rather coarsely striate (
Fig. 28
).
